e Kauffman Foundation’s Brink Lindsey surmises that the most developed nations, like the U.S., need ever more freedom and entrepreneurship to grow. Developing nations can simply adopt the world’s leading edge technologies and business practices. Their growth path is relatively clear. Not so for us. Because we define the economic and technological frontier, we must keep pushing forward into an uncertain future.

